passages.text: August 28, 2025 08:53 AM GMT

We hosted a post-results NDR with the Chairman and CFO attending. Management addresses investor queries on recurring profit trajectory, development margin, business transformation and ROE enhancement. We reiterate CR Land as our Top Pick.
Recurring profits to account for \(50\%\) of earnings in the 15th Five- Year Plan, backed by continued mall alpha via new construction and M&A with the help of REITs.
Development margin to bottom at mid- teens \(\%\) in 2025- 26 amid diminishing drag of old inventory, leading to potential ROE rebound in 2027.
Maintaining a stable dividend payout in the next few years, with potential upside in the 15th Five- Year Plan amid business transformation.

Mall expansion: On top of new mall constructions, the Chairman sees CR Land could potentially add 3- 5 malls via M&A p.a. with the help of public/private/quasi REITs in the medium term to expand its portfolio to \(\sim 200\) malls by 2030.

REIT spin- off: CR Land aims to divest Rmb5- 10bn of mature mall assets into REIT platform annually. Management guided M&A malls could be put into operation in \(\sim 6\) months after revamp, balancing the disposal impact to keep steady rental growth.

Recurring income: The Chairman expects recurring income to account for \(40\%\) of revenue and \(50\%\) of earnings ( \(>Rmb15bn\) ) in the 15th Five- Year Plan, implying \(>7\%\) CAGR over 2024- 2030.

Development margin: CFO guided \(13 - 15\%\) GPM for unbooked sales, and expects it to bottom in 2025- 26 given 1) diminishing pressure on asset impairment amid reducing old inventory ( \(Rmb100bn\) saleable resources as of 1H), and 2) better quality of new projects added in recent years. Cumulatively, CR Land has made Rmb44bn asset impairments on a gross basis, taking one of the most prudent approaches among users.

Property sales: CR Land prioritizes profits over scale (maintain top- 3 sales ranking). With more prudent and focused landbanking in \(\sim 30\) selected top- tier cities, the CFO foresees project- level net margin recovering back to \(\sim 10\%\) in the medium term.

ROE enhancement: Management expects ROE to rebound in 2027 amid recovering development margin, and targets to further improve it by boosting asset turnover via revitalizing low- efficiency assets (e.g., office buildings).

Market- cap management: The Chairman showcased strong commitment to enhancing shareholder return with stable payout ratio in the next few years, and sees potential for gradual payout increase in the 15th Five- Year Plan amid business transformation, although management share incentive scheme is still not in sight.
MORGAN STANLEY ASIA LIMITED+
China Resources Land Ltd. (1109. HK, 1109 HK)
China Property | China
